FIGS 1
; 
6A–F
; 
9

Head profile fairly blunt: 74–81° [78°]. Mouth downturned, maxilla extending to vertical through posterior margin of pupil. Orbital cirrus length equal to pupil diameter, flat and at least slightly widened and bifurcate at the end in juveniles, with several short branches in adults (
Fig. 6B
); nasal cirrus a simple flat flap. Dorsal-fin crest of mature males tall and triangular, up to 3 times the height of dorsal fin, of females to 1.7 times the height of dorsal fin. Dorsalfin spines with a single filament at the tips. Scales on dorsal, caudal, and pectoral fin bases.
